title: Query parameters for Find Address — create_params_kv_punktsok
text: radius integer value radius query, whole meters. crs integer vector input output coordinate reference system. what: Query parameters for Get Address — create_params_kv_sok
title: Query parameters for Get Address — create_params_kv_sok
text: Accepted query parameters Kartverket's endpoint /sok.

title: Query parameters for Get Address — create_params_kv_sok
code: create_params_kv_sok(   search = NULL,   fuzzy = FALSE,   search_mode = c("AND", "OR"),   object_type = c("Both", "Vegadresse", "Matrikkeladresse"),   mun_code = NULL,   mun_name = NULL,   address_name = NULL,   address_text = NULL,   address_ext_name = NULL,   address_code = NULL,   address_number = NULL,   address_letter = NULL,   cadastral_unit_number = NULL,   property_unit_number = NULL,   leasehold_number = NULL,   sub_code = NULL,   unit_number = NULL,   postal_town = NULL,   postal_code = NULL,   crs = 4258,   ascii_compatible = TRUE,   page = 0,   size = 1000 )

title: Query parameters for Get Address — create_params_kv_sok
text: search Norwegian address. example: 'munkegata 1 trondheim'. fuzzy TRUE fuzzy search provided addresses conducted. compatible use wildcards (*). search_mode Modify search parameter boolean logic. Use select whether search require search parameter found match, whether sufficient hits one parameter. E.g. search = 'munkegata 1 trondheim' & search_mode = '' return everything contains 'munkegata' / number '1' / 'trondheim'. Defaults ''. object_type Specify type address query, either road address ('Vegadresse'), cadastral address ('Matrikkeladresse') . Defaults . mun_code character string Norwegian municipality code. mun_name character string name Norwegian municipality. address_name character string name street, road, path, space area entered cadastre. address_text character string name street, road, path, space area entered cadastre. address_ext_name character string inherited property unit name, name institution building used part official address. address_code integer value uniquely identifies addressable streets, roads, paths, places areas entered cadastre within municipality. address_number integer value representing part address number (house number), e.g. 23. address_letter character string representing part address number (house number), e.g. 'B' 23B. search addresses without letter, include 'letter =' search string without filling value. cadastral_unit_number integer value cadastral unit number property. part cadastral address road addresses introduced, road address's link cadastral unit. property_unit_number integer value property unit number property. part cadastral address road addresses introduced, road address's link cadastral unit. leasehold_number integer value leasehold number property. part cadastral address road addresses introduced, road address's link cadastral unit. sub_code integer value subcode (undernummer) cadastral addresses cadastral, property leasehold number. unit_number integer value unit number (formerly called flat number) apartment multi-dwelling buildings. letter first two numbers indicate floor, last two indicate apartment's number floor, counted left right. example: 'H0102', 'K0101'. postal_town character string name Norwegian postal town (place). postal_code character string Norwegian postal code. crs desired coordinate reference system output. Default value ETRS89 latitude longitude data (EPSG:4258). See details. ascii_compatible TRUE (default) returned data ASCII compatible. page integer value page query. Defaults 0 (first page). size integer value size page. Defaults 1000.

what: Find addresses within a geographical area — find_address_from_point
title: Find addresses within a geographical area — find_address_from_point
text: Search Norwegian addresses within certain radius geographical point.

title: Find addresses within a geographical area — find_address_from_point
code: find_address_from_point(   x,   radius = 50,   crs = 4258,   closest = FALSE,   ...,   simplify = TRUE,   raw_response = FALSE )

title: Find addresses within a geographical area — find_address_from_point
text: x vector list latitude longitude coordinates. radius integer value radius query, whole meters. crs integer vector input output coordinate reference system. Default value ETRS89 latitude longitude data (EPSG:4258). closest TRUE address closest geographical point returned. ... Additional arguments passed API call. simplify TRUE (default), single data.frame returned. Ignored raw_response set TRUE. raw_response TRUE list class noAPI returned, including raw httr2_response.

title: Find addresses within a geographical area — find_address_from_point
text: data.frame list

title: Find addresses within a geographical area — find_address_from_point
text: use cases ETRS89 (EPSG:4258) WSG84 (EPSG:4326) can considered equal, users aware slight shift axes two coordinate systems. high precision needed crs set 4326. Advanced users might want look additional possible parameters. list accepted query parameters see create_params_kv_punktsok() refer API documentation details (Norwegian ). function returns data.frame default. prefer output list can set simplify FALSE. can useful keep programmatically track failed queries. set raw_response TRUE, raw response API returned together parsed response. Note response returned silently.

title: Get countries — get_countries
text: Get country codes (alpha-3) based ISO 3166-1 standard, adjusted data Statistics Norway.

title: Get countries — get_countries
code: get_countries(   year = format(Sys.Date(), "%Y"),   include_notes = FALSE,   simplify = TRUE,   raw_response = FALSE )

title: Get countries — get_countries
text: year year codes valid . include_notes notes included . simplify TRUE (default), single data.frame returned. Ignored raw_response set TRUE. raw_response TRUE list class noAPI returned, including raw httr2_response.

title: Get countries — get_countries
text: data.frame list

title: Get countries — get_countries
text: Fetches countries country codes (alpha-3) given year based ISO 3166-1 standard. list includes special codes XUK XXX unknown citizenship stateless persons, respectively. codes used official statistics Statistics Norway. years 1974 present supported. function defaults current year. notes enabled include_notes, column note added data.frame. Notes stated code reference following order (alpha-2, alpha-3, num-3, SSB-3), example Norway (, , 578, 000). See Statistics Norway's webpage information code specification. function returns data.frame default. prefer output list can set simplify FALSE. can useful keep programmatically track failed queries. set raw_response TRUE, raw response API returned together parsed response. Note response returned silently.

title: Get entity — get_entity
text: Fetch information entity Central Coordinating Register Legal Entities (Enhetsregisteret) based entity's name organisation number.

title: Get entity — get_entity
code: get_entity(entity, type = NULL, simplify = TRUE, raw_response = FALSE)

title: Get entity — get_entity
text: entity Norwegian organisation number company name. type Optional. Type entity query. Either main, sub NULL (default). See details. simplify TRUE (default), single data.frame returned. Ignored raw_response set TRUE. raw_response TRUE list class noAPI returned, including raw httr2_response.

title: Get entity — get_entity
text: data.frame list

title: Get entity — get_entity
text: Users aware queries entity names numbers handled somewhat differently. default (type = NULL) queries numbers first send requests registry main entities, also query registry sub-entities case information found first query. ensures entity number still use return valid response. names however get_entity() query registry main entities, unless type explicitly set sub. information use sub-entities can found . function returns data.frame default. prefer output list can set simplify FALSE. can useful keep programmatically track failed queries. set raw_response TRUE, raw response API returned together parsed response. Note response returned silently. See API documentation details (Norwegian ).

title: Get entity — get_entity
code: # Get entity by number df <- get_entity(974760843)  # Get entity by name df <- get_entity('Riksrevisjonen')  # Get multiple entities df <- get_entity(c(974760843, 971524960))  # Get information on sub-entities (number) df <- get_entity(999178197)  #' # Get information on sub-entities (name) df <- get_entity('Kuben Yrkesarena', type = 'sub')

title: Get exchange rate — get_exchange_rate
text: Fetch exchange rates Norges Bank.

title: Get exchange rate — get_exchange_rate
code: get_exchange_rate(   currency,   frequency = c("daily", "monthly", "annual"),   n_obs = 10,   start = NULL,   end = NULL,   simplify = TRUE,   raw_response = FALSE )

title: Get exchange rate — get_exchange_rate
text: currency currency fetch data . frequency Frequency data. Can daily, monthly annual. Defaults daily. n_obs number observations fetch. See details. start first date fetch data . end last date fetch data . simplify TRUE (default), single data.frame returned. Ignored raw_response set TRUE. raw_response TRUE list class noAPI returned, including raw httr2_response.

title: Get exchange rate — get_exchange_rate
text: data.frame list

title: Get exchange rate — get_exchange_rate
text: Currency must formatted three letter ISO 3166 code. list available country codes can found Norges Bank. can fetch observations several currencies passing character vector. want include currencies, can set currency argument . Note number observations limited 20 retrieving currencies. default, 10 latest observations returned. can adjust number observations setting n_obs positive integer. can also fetch exchange rates specific time period setting arguments start end. arguments accept date format %Y-%m-%d (YYYY-MM-DD). function returns data.frame default. prefer output list can set simplify FALSE. can useful keep programmatically track failed queries. set raw_response TRUE, raw response API returned together parsed response. Note response returned silently.

title: Get Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) — get_industrial_codes
text: Get Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) based NACE standard.

title: Get Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) — get_industrial_codes
code: get_industrial_codes(   year = format(Sys.Date(), "%Y"),   include_notes = FALSE,   simplify = TRUE,   raw_response = FALSE )

title: Get Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) — get_industrial_codes
text: year year codes valid . include_notes notes included . simplify TRUE (default), single data.frame returned. Ignored raw_response set TRUE. raw_response TRUE list class noAPI returned, including raw httr2_response.

title: Get Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) — get_industrial_codes
text: data.frame list

title: Get Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) — get_industrial_codes
text: Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) primarily statistical standard basis coding units according important activities Statistics Norway's Business register Central Coordinating Register Legal Entities. SIC2007 based NACE Rev. 2. See Statistics Norway's webpage information code specification. years 1994 present supported. function defaults current year. notes enabled include_notes, column note added data.frame. function returns data.frame default. prefer output list can set simplify FALSE. can useful keep programmatically track failed queries. set raw_response TRUE, raw response API returned together parsed response. Note response returned silently.

title: Get municipalities and counties — get_municipalities
text: Get Norwegian municipalities counties, respective codes, given year.

title: Get municipalities and counties — get_municipalities
code: get_municipalities(   year = format(Sys.Date(), "%Y"),   include_notes = FALSE,   simplify = TRUE,   raw_response = FALSE )  get_counties(   year = format(Sys.Date(), "%Y"),   include_notes = FALSE,   simplify = TRUE,   raw_response = FALSE )  get_adm_units(year = format(Sys.Date(), "%Y"), simplify = TRUE)

title: Get municipalities and counties — get_municipalities
text: year year codes valid . include_notes notes included . simplify TRUE (default), single data.frame returned. Ignored raw_response set TRUE. raw_response TRUE list class noAPI returned, including raw httr2_response.

title: Get municipalities and counties — get_municipalities
text: data.frame list

title: Get municipalities and counties — get_municipalities
text: get_municipalities() supports years 1977, get_counties() supports years 1972. get_adm_units() wrapper function get municipality county codes function call. three functions default current year. functions returns data.frame default. prefer output list can set simplify FALSE. can useful keep programmatically track failed queries. set raw_response TRUE, raw response API returned together parsed response. Note response returned silently.

title: Get SSB table metadata — get_ssb_metadata
text: Fetch metadata ready-made tables Statistics Norway (SSB).

title: Get SSB table metadata — get_ssb_metadata
code: get_ssb_metadata(data_tag = NULL)

title: Get SSB table metadata — get_ssb_metadata
text: data_tag Optional. Data tag filter .

title: Get SSB table metadata — get_ssb_metadata
text: data.frame

title: Get SSB table metadata — get_ssb_metadata
text: function returns overview available ready-made tables produced Statistics Norway. Note metadata updated daily 05.00 11.30 , can lead API unavailable five minutes. See API documentation details.

title: Get SSB table metadata — get_ssb_metadata
code: # Get all metadata ssb_metadata <- get_ssb_metadata()  # Get a subset containing certain tags ssb_metadata_arbeidskraft <- get_ssb_metadata(data_tag = 'arbeidskraft')

title: Get SSB table — get_ssb_table
text: Fetch ready-made tables Statistics Norway (SSB).

title: Get SSB table — get_ssb_table
code: get_ssb_table(id)

title: Get SSB table — get_ssb_table
text: id table ID. Corresponds ID variable metadata.

title: Get SSB table — get_ssb_table
text: data.frame

title: Get SSB table — get_ssb_table
text: function returns ready-made table produced Statistics Norway, based provided table ID. list available IDs can found get_ssb_metadata(). Note metadata updated daily 05.00 11.30 , can lead API unavailable five minutes. See API documentation details.

title: Get SSB table — get_ssb_table
code: # Get table with ID '1104' df <- get_ssb_table('1104')
